programme.title: Live Test Cricket
programme.sub-title: New Zealand v England: First Test Day Five
programme.desc: New Zealand v England. New Zealand v England. Coverage of the fifth and final day of the First Test in the two-match series, which takes place at Eden Park in Auckland. The sides last met here in this format five years ago when the contest ended as a draw, with Peter Fulton and Matt Prior starring with the bat for the hosts and tourists respectively.(n)

programme.title: Live Test Cricket
programme.sub-title: South Africa v Australia: Third Test Day Five
programme.desc: South Africa v Australia. Coverage of day five of the Third Test from Newlands in Cape Town, as the four-match series continues. The series is currently tied at 1-1 following the two previous encounters, with Australia having taken a 1-0 lead with a 118-run victory in Durban, before the hosts claimed a six-wicket triumph in Port Elizabeth last time out, thanks largely to the bowling of Kagiso Rabada, who took 11 wickets over the two innings.(n)

programme.desc: Spain v Argentina (Kick-off 8.30pm). Coverage of the friendly match at Estadio Wanda Metropolitano in Madrid. The last meeting between the sides was back in September 2010, when the South Americans claimed an emphatic 4-1 home win in a friendly just two months after Spain had been crowned world champions.(n)
